<TITLE> Three firms willing to sponsor WC Twenty20 team </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 16 (bdnews24.com) - Only three companies have submitted tenders to sponsor the national cricket team in the ICC Twenty20 World Cup in South Africa in September. Ahmed Sajjadul Alam Bobby briefed reporters at a press conference at the Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) office in Gulshan Thursday. He said: "We received three tenders for sponsoring the national team in the Twenty20 World Cup." "No tender was floated to sponsor the team's strips." "The name of the team's sponsor will be disclosed following the talks." "We will arrange the strip's sponsor through negotiations. The short duration of the tournament may discourage any sponsors to come forward." Bobby added that the board would arrive at a decision by early September regarding the appointment of a national coach. Bobby continued: "We will decide at that time whether to interview the short-listed coaches or expand the list of coaches further." He said that the meeting had also decided to form a committee, comprising former cricketers, coaches and organisers, to recommend some longer term plans for domestic cricket
